caption.title: MMP9 promotes the degradation of junctional protein and CA16 entry into the CNS, which leading to CNS lesion in CA16-infected rhesus monkeys.
caption.p: a Junctional protein expression in thalamus of different treated rhesus monkeys. b Statistical analysis of the quantitative value of intensity about the blots. The ratios indicated the intensity of the bands compare to the GAPDH. c The efficacy of CA16 infections in thalamus of different treated rhesus monkeys. CA16-VP1 and the cell nucleus are indicated by green and mazarine, respectively. d Statistical analysis of viral infection rates. The ratios indicated the infected cells compared to the total cells from ten different visual fields. e Histopathological changes in the thalamus and lungs of different treated rhesus monkeys. The green arrow points to a place where pathological changes are obvious
